        TOP 35 REVIEW

        I got too tired to do the whole top 40 icl

        S TIER

        Lose Control - Teddy Swims [33] - I've said this so many times about Teddy in so many different places but his voice just isn't beatable. I hope this man goes on to have even more hits when his next album releases in January, maybe even finally getting the number 1 he deserves.

        Bad Dreams - Teddy Swims [25] - Just incredible, so glad I knew about Teddy when this single was released because it just blew me away.

        A Bar Song (Tipsy) - Shaboozey [30] - This man is so underrated in the UK I swear, sometimes makes me wish we had the same chart as the US, Shaboozey deserves all those weeks at number one.

        The Door - Teddy Swims [12] - Again, like Lose Control and Bad Dreams, just is unbeatable.

        Die With A Smile - Lady Gaga & Bruno Mars [17] - The collab we never knew we needed. Need I say more?

        A TIER

        APT. - ROSÉ & Bruno Mars [2] - Catchy and will not leave my head ever, I will say that I am not big on K-Pop, so Bruno kind of carried this song for me, but nonetheless a hit.

        It's ok I'm ok - Tate McRae [35] - Would be S Tier if I could understand what she's saying I guess.

        The Emptiness Machine - Linkin Park [34] - Incredible but not quite S Tier material.

        Move - Adam Port, Stryv, Keinemusik, Orso & Malachiii [13] - This is honestly a vibe! I see why people like this song.

        Bed Chem - Sabrina Carpenter [9] - Probably Sabrina's only song to chart which hasn't been completely corrupted by airplay which makes it good.

        BIRDS OF A FEATHER - Billie Eilish [21] - Really catchy melody and soothing vocals.

        PRADA - Casso, RAYE & D-Block Europe [31] - I just found this song how the did I miss this?

        WILDFLOWER - Billie Eilish [18] - Listenable, Billie's vocals are just heavenly though.

        Somedays - Jazzy, D.O.D & Sonny Fodera [5] - I will admit, I do quite like this one. I feel like the singer's voice could be a little clearer but aside from that it's actually okay!

        Night Changes - One Direction [14] - I wasn't around when 1D was a big thing, so maybe this resonates with you a lot more than it does with me. Regardless, this is probably the best of their work. Rest in peace Liam Payne.

        Story of My Life - One Direction [23] - Lovely song which feels relevant at the moment.

        B TIER

        I Love You, I'm Sorry - Gracie Abrams [4] - I am a fan of Gracie's music and this song is no difference to that, but as you'll find for her other songs, I don't really get anything out of it. Take Lose Control [33] for example. That song makes me feel good, and I love to listen to it. Gracie's songs don't spark that reaction in me whatsoever.

        Disease - Lady Gaga [7] - Very middle of the road, despite having possibly one of the best music videos of the year.

        Diet Pepsi - Addison Rae [10] - Decent but also if radio stations play it to the same level they corrupted Sabrina with (which seems to already be happening over on Capital) then I'm not interested

        Chart Review In Short 01/11/24

        Something funny about Halloween should be put here, but I'm pretty sure everyone treated yesterday like the most boring of Thursdays. I mean, the magic's just gone from that, surely. Especially during the UK charts. When you've got just one day left to make a difference, there's only one outcome. Nothing. Which is also what has happened to Sabrina Carpenter this week. Because she's getting absolutely no plaudits for hitting ACR and tumbing down to No.11. You spend 9 weeks at the top and completely fumble it. At least try and not fall apart so horrendously next time, OK? Thus, the brand new Number 1 goes to the 8th most famous Gigi according to Wikipedia, as Sailor Song has spectacularly ended up as the most popular song of the moment. I say spectacularly, it sounds like a Vampire Weekend B-side, and hardly the kind of thing that, in theory, should be the biggest thing on the planet. Still though, props to you Ms. Perez, and I'm sure your home town of Hackensack, New Jersey (great name for a town in my humble opinion) will be getting that open bus-top parade as we speak. It's also one in the face of Capital's Big Top 40 where this song hasn't even hit the Top FORTY. And they have the temerity to say that chart is official.

        INSERT A PROUD COMMENT ABOUT HOW SHE'S REPPING THE LGBT COMMUNITY HERE 🏳️‍🌈

        Elsewhere, Lady Gaga has clearly decided that the massive success of Die With A Smile was insanely pointless, and has treated new release Disease with all the hype you'd expect from someone who duets with the most streamed artist on Earth right now (thanks Mr. Mars). Small problem with that though. Disease sounds like a Born This Way album track in terms of sound and energy, and sees her vocal tread dangeorusly close to the warbled tones of Becky Hill.
